--><ns2353:section xmlns:ns2353="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook" xml:id="resources.information.platforms.linux.introduction.whatIsLinux">

  <ns2354:title xmlns:ns2354="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">What is Linux</ns2354:title>
  <ns2355:para xmlns:ns2355="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
    Linux is a free, open source Unix-based scalable operating system initially developed for 
    the Intel PC platform but now available for a wide spectrum of platforms ranging from
    PDAs to mainframes. Linux is published under the GNU Public License (GPL).
  </ns2355:para>
